[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man critically ill after car 'deliberately driven at him'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man is in a critical condition after he was hit by a car in a leisure centre car park that police believe may have been deliberately driven at him.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Emergency services were called following the collision in the car park of Great North Leisure Park, Finchley, at about 20:30 BST on Wednesday.
The Met Police believe the victim - a man aged in his 20s - was assaulted before the car was driven at him.
The car - a white BMW - was abandoned at the site. No arrests have been made.
